  "prompt": "What should be my first Quora question?",
  "response": "When choosing your first Quora question, consider asking something that:\n\n1. Reflects your genuine curiosity or need for information\n2. Is specific enough to elicit useful, focused answers\n3. Has the potential to spark interesting discussions\n4. Relates to a topic you're passionate about or want to learn more about\n\nHere are a few examples of good first questions:\n\n1. \"What are some lesser-known but highly effective time management techniques?\"\n2. \"How can someone new to coding start contributing to open-source projects?\"\n3. \"What are the most important things to consider when choosing a career path in your 20s?\"\n4. \"What are some unique cultural traditions from around the world that more people should know about?\"\n\nRemember, the key is to ask a question that you're genuinely interested in learning more about. This will make it more likely that you'll engage with the answers and follow-up questions, helping you get the most out of the Quora platform.",
